Paper: hep-th/9408176

Date: 1994-08-31

Title: The Weinberg Propagators

Comments: HPATEX.STY used, 6pp

Journal-ref: Helv.Phys.Acta 70 (1997) 697-702

An analog of the $j=1/2$ Feynman-Dyson propagator is presented in theframework of the $j=1$ Weinberg's theory. The basis for this construction isthe concept of the Weinberg field as a system of four field functions differingby parity and by dual transformations.